title: Four BWAC teams, Sandusky, Deckerville earn AP votes
text:
Four BWAC teams, Sandusky, Deckerville earn AP votes Matt Sheehan, Times Herald 3:20 p.m. EDT September 30, 2015 Cros-Lex's William Bass celebrates a sack along with Luke Wilson during a football game Friday, September 11, 2015 at Cros-Lex High School. (Photo: Jeffrey M Smith) 3 CONNECT 3 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
With the fifth week of high school football wrapped up, the latest Associated Press football rankings have a handful of area teams on notice. 
Croswell-Lexington is the highest ranked area team in their respective division, as they are No. 5 in Division 4 with 26 points. Country Day, who faced Port Huron in week one, is on top of Division 4 with 48 points. 
Richmond and Algonac are No. 12 and 13, respectively, in Division 5. The Blue Devils racked up three points while the Muskrats earned two. Almont, who topped Richmond last Friday in double overtime, is ranked No. 6 in the division with 27 points. 
Sandusky also picked up two points in Division 7 polling, earning the No. 13 rank. 
Deckerville is also represented in the 8-man football division they've been rolling in, earning the No. 4 ranking with 55 points. Lawrence is ranked No. 1 with 87 points.
